comments: Holmgren (OKC) briefly places a resting hand on Williamson's (NOP) side as he sets the pick.
Holmgren (OKC) makes incidental contact to Williamson's (NOP) arm as he attempts to retrieve the incoming pass.
Nance Jr. (NOP) cleanly deflects the loose ball away from Holmgren (OKC) as both players pursue the rebound.
Jones (NOP) absorbs the contact initiated by Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) during the drive.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) releases the pass prior to landing on the floor.
Nance Jr. (NOP) briefly places his hand on Holmgren's (OKC) side as he establishes a screening position during the pick.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) reaches in and makes clean contact with the ball during Jones's (NOP) drive.  He places his left arm against his back, but the contact is marginal.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) takes a legal dribble and does not place any part of his hand underneath the ball or bring the ball to a pause.
Williamson (NOP) releases from Dort (OKC) as both players engage as the screen is set.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) briefly places his hand to Murphy III's (NOP) body as he attempts to get around the screen, which he is able to move through.
Jones (NOP) establishes himself in Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and absorbs the incoming contact during the screen.
Nance Jr. (NOP) slightly extends his forearm into Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) body as he sets the screen.
Williams (OKC) establishes the ball in the frontcourt within eight seconds.
Holmgren (OKC) collapses his arm and does not deliver contact when he and Murphy III (NOP) engage as the screen is set.
Williams (OKC) releases from McCollum (NOP) as both players come together at the start of the drive.
Nance Jr. (NOP) extends his leg out and makes intentional foot to ball contact during the inbounds pass.
Giddey (OKC) releases the inbounds pass within five seconds.
The ball is last touched by Nance Jr. (NOP) prior to it going out of bounds.
Marshall (NOP) commits a take foul on Holmgren (OKC).
Williamson (NOP) commits a take foul on Williams (OKC).
Williams (OKC) briefly touches McCollum's (NOP) side after the release of his jump shot attempt, but the contact is marginal and does not affect his ability to return to the floor.
